rComments: Thierry's C09 for Winter 2019 was a great course to be in. His lectures were really fast and covered a lot of content, but it was all interesting concepts and modern technologies. His assignments and exercises built on top of each other and he was fairly generous with grading. His finals are incredibly fair, and there's a high chance at a good mark
Great guy, carried me through D27, thanks Abi Sans!

Sans is alright, better than most other professors. He doesn't show you that he cares when you talk to him but he does give it thought. His assignments and labs are clear, they are bite sized and have a clear learning objective. His exams are tough, but you can still ace them if you're well versed with git and Java.
Worst Professor ever. He copies slides from other courses, does not know what he is talking about, and is intolerant. If you ask questions, he is either not able to answer them or he gets aggressive.

He is not a bad teacher, but he is somewhat impatient. To get more knowledge you have to be patient so ask questions whenever you can. Thierry is more like a real computer engineer so he act creatively, and really quickly. I think thats why he feels impatient.
Easy if got a group of friends to point eachother in right direction. Weekly labs/assments but bite sized.

He is not very patient when you ask him questions. Sometimes he can't read what you wrote before he answers your question on piazza. I can tell he is trying to be a good prof and he expects a lot from us but his impatience really bothers me a lot. Everything else about him is good so I gave him a passing grade.
